description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;INTERNAL APPLICANTS ONLY&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are looking for an experienced administrator to join the WK People, projects and business team for a 6 month secondment whilst our Business Support Manager is away on secondment until next April. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We need somebody with a good knowledge of West Kent Services and systems, with advanced IT skills and experience of working with our partners including our CCG and PCNs. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The role involves being able to juggle lots of urgent priorities, working with people from all levels of the organisation as well as external stakeholders in an environment of constant change and uncertainty. You will need to be able to think on your feet and confidently and confidentially manage a range of issues and situations. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We welcome applications from all groups in the community and will accommodate needs and make adjustments wherever possible. We welcome applications from individuals from diverse backgrounds and those covered by the Equalities Act.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;This post is open to Internal Candidates only.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;For further information on the role please contact Caroline Hanlon on 07775552081. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Interviews to be held on 11th November 2020&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameCaroline HanlonJob titlePeople and Business PartnerEmail addresschanlon@nhs.netTelephone number07775 552081&lt;/p&gt;
